bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Version-Release number of selected component: gnome-terminal-3.22.1-1.fc25
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.8.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/libexec/gnome-terminal-server crash_function: after_process_all_updates executable: /usr/libexec/gnome-terminal-server global_pid: 2939 kernel: 4.8.10-300.fc25.x86_64 pkg_fingerprint: 4089 D8F2 FDB1 9C98 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (5 frames) #2 after_process_all_updates at gdkwindow.c:4033 #3 gdk_window_process_all_updates at gdkwindow.c:4099 #4 update_timeout at vte.cc:10710 #9 g_main_context_iteration at gmain.c:3990 #10 g_application_run at gapplication.c:2381
Potential duplicate: bug 1390168

Similar problem has been detected:
$ WAYLAND_DISPLAY= gnome-terminal
reporter: libreport-2.8.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/libexec/gnome-terminal-server crash_function: after_process_all_updates executable: /usr/libexec/gnome-terminal-server global_pid: 20201 kernel: 4.10.6-200.fc25.x86_64 package: gnome-terminal-3.22.1-5.fc25 pkg_fingerprint: 4089 D8F2 FDB1 9C98 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project reason: gnome-terminal-server killed by SIGSEGV runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1001

That is, from an xterm window, I attempted to start gnome-terminal under XWayland:
$ WAYLAND_DISPLAY= gnome-terminal Error: Message recipient disconnected from message bus without replying $
(and the server process segfaulted, causing an ABRT popup).

I looks like I forgot to mention that this issue showed up for the first time when I ran
GDK_BACKEND=x11 gnome-terminal
as a test in a GNOME on Wayland session.
This issue also affects the current Fedora 26 branch.

Similar problem has been detected:
I don't really know what happened. I had a bunch of terminals open (some of them for a long time: ~days) and then when I tried to open a new one all of them crashed.
reporter: libreport-2.8.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/libexec/gnome-terminal-server crash_function: after_process_all_updates executable: /usr/libexec/gnome-terminal-server global_pid: 8153 kernel: 4.10.11-200.fc25.x86_64 package: gnome-terminal-3.22.1-5.fc25 pkg_fingerprint: 4089 D8F2 FDB1 9C98 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project reason: gnome-terminal-server killed by SIGSEGV runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1001

(In reply to Dan Dragomir from comment #19) Please update your system and reboot. If the issue persists, add a corresponding comment, thanks. The use case which triggered this bug in the first place should have been fixed some time ago; indeed, I cannot reproduce the crash on my system any longer.
